05/05/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Interpol announced on Tuesday (May 4th) that a suspected high-profile jewel thief has been arrested on the Serbian-Montenegrin border. Bojan Vuckovic, 24, is an alleged member of the so-called Pink Panthers crime group. He is wanted by Austrian police in connection with the robbery of a jewellery shop in Vienna in November 2008. The Pink Panthers, believed to be comprised of mostly Balkan members, are suspected of stealing jewels worth more than 250m euros from various stores worldwide. (RTCG, Portal Analitika, RTS, AP - 04/05/10)
